- 'estimators' refer to users who have an `estimator_id` in the `estimator_performance` table;
- 'performance ratings' are numerical values representing the quality of work, typically on a scale from 1 to 5;
- 'the realm where the highest performance shines the brightest' means the results are ordered by the average performance rating in descending order, highlighting the top performers.

sql:
SELECT AVG(ep.performance_rating) AS average_performance_rating
FROM estimator_performance ep
INNER JOIN (
    SELECT DISTINCT estimator_id
    FROM estimator_notes
) AS notes_estimator ON ep.estimator_id = notes_estimator.estimator_id;

